# Environment Configuration

## Required Variables

### OpenAI API
```bash
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
```

## Optional Variables (for future features)

### Database (for authentication & quotas)
```bash
# PostgreSQL connection string
# Example: postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/tts_db
DATABASE_URL=

# Prisma connection pooling URL (for production)
DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED=
```

### Rate Limiting
```bash
# Redis URL for distributed rate limiting (optional)
# If not set, uses in-memory rate limiting
# Example: redis://localhost:6379
REDIS_URL=
```

### Application Configuration
```bash
# Environment mode
NODE_ENV=development

# Application URL (used for CORS and redirects)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Free tier character limit per month
NEXT_PUBLIC_MAX_FREE_CHARACTERS=10000

# Enable/disable monetization (quotas)
# Set to 'true' to enable quotas, 'false' for unlimited usage
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_MONETIZATION=false
```

## Development vs Production

### Development (.env.local)
```bash
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
NODE_ENV=development
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### Production
```bash
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
NODE_ENV=production
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
REDIS_URL=redis://...
```